The specific epithet refers to Parque Nacional Yasuni , where most of the collections of this new species come from. At present, 2700 vascular plant species are documented from Yasuni , including a high diversity of lianas, epiphytes, and ferns; it is estimated its flora comprises approximately 3213 species; Yasuni is also home to ca. 1570 species of birds, fishes, mammals, amphibians and reptiles ( Bass et al. 2010 ;
Perez et al. 2014
). The description of
Virola yasuniana
is one step closer to a full documentation of this region.

