Virola yasuniana

is Vulnerable following IUCN criterion B2a. It is known from two localities, has an EOO of 117,581 km2, and an AOO of 32 km2. This species benefits from its occurrence in the 
Yasuni
National Park of Ecuador, which experiences very low rates of deforestation (
Bass et al. 2010
; 
van der Hoek 2017
), even while the broader region is experiencing land use changes (
Heredia-R et al. 2021
).
